\frac{1}{2}(P\sqrt{1-P^2} + \arcsin P)
\int_0^P \sqrt{1-x^2}dx.
x=\sin \psi
dx = \cos \psi\:  d\psi
\int_0^{\arcsin P} \cos^2 \psi\: d\psi = \frac{1}{2}\int_0^{\arcsin P} (1+\cos{2\psi}) \: d\psi
= \frac{1}{2}(\arcsin P + \frac{1}{2}\sin(2\arcsin P)) = \frac{1}{2}(\arcsin P + P\sqrt{1-P^2}).
\cos \theta
0 \le \theta \le \pi/2
\theta/2
\pi / 4
\theta
1/2 \cos \theta \sin \theta = 1/4 \sin 2\theta
\theta/2 - 1/4 \sin 2\theta
1/4 \left( \pi + \sin 2 \theta - 2\theta \right).
